abstract: U.S. Democratic presidential contender Pete Buttigieg held his first fundraiser open to press coverage on Tuesday after facing pressure from rival Elizabeth Warren to be more transparent.
snippet: U.S. Democratic presidential contender Pete Buttigieg held his first fundraiser open to press coverage on Tuesday after facing pressure from rival Elizabeth Warren to be more transparent.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — U.S. Democratic presidential contender Pete Buttigieg held his first fundraiser open to press coverage on Tuesday after facing pressure from rival Elizabeth Warren to be more transparent.
headline_main: Buttigieg Opens Fundraisers to Media After Tension Over Donor Influence
headline_print_headline: Buttigieg Opens Fundraisers to Media After Tension Over Donor Influence

abstract: President Trump told supporters at a Pennsylvania rally that they were “lucky I became your president” before denouncing the impeachment effort.
snippet: President Trump told supporters at a Pennsylvania rally that they were “lucky I became your president” before denouncing the impeachment effort.
lead_paragraph: HERSHEY, Pa. — President Trump told supporters on Tuesday at a rally in Pennsylvania that they were “lucky I became your president” before entering into a screed against House Democrats for introducing articles of impeachment against him, calling the effort “flimsy” and “the lightest impeachment in the history of our country.”

abstract: Under a settlement, the president admitted he had used his charity to bolster his campaign and settle business debts.
snippet: Under a settlement, the president admitted he had used his charity to bolster his campaign and settle business debts.
lead_paragraph: President Trump has paid $2 million to eight charities as part of a settlement in which the president admitted he misused funds raised by the Donald J. Trump Foundation to promote his presidential bid and pay off business debts, the New York State attorney general said on Tuesday.

headline_main: Trump Pays $2 Million to 8 Charities for Misuse of Foundation

abstract: The last-minute debate over how broad a case to bring reflects the competing demands on Democrats from within their own party and their determination to appear as unified as possible.
snippet: The last-minute debate over how broad a case to bring reflects the competing demands on Democrats from within their own party and their determination to appear as unified as possible.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Speaker Nancy Pelosi and her top lieutenants huddled in her office last week as Representative Jerrold Nadler, Democrat of New York, who oversees the Judiciary Committee, made the case that the House should take up three articles of impeachment against President Trump. Representative Richard E. Neal, Democrat of Massachusetts and the chairman of the Ways and Means Committee, countered that there should only be two.

headline_main: Seeking Unity on Impeachment, Democrats Decided Against Mueller Charges
headline_print_headline: Seeking Unity, Democrats Decided Against Charge Based on Mueller’s Report

abstract: House lawyers sought to dismiss as moot a lawsuit brought by a former Trump adviser, but his lawyers asked a federal judge to rule anyway on his duty to comply with a House subpoena.
snippet: House lawyers sought to dismiss as moot a lawsuit brought by a former Trump adviser, but his lawyers asked a federal judge to rule anyway on his duty to comply with a House subpoena.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A federal judge on Tuesday heard final arguments in a case brought by Charles M. Kupperman, President Trump’s former deputy national security adviser, who asked for clarity from a federal court about whether he must testify to Congress amid a constitutional clash between House investigators and the White House.

abstract: A Methodist church in Southern California has turned a classic Christmas tradition - the Nativity scene depicting the birth of Jesus - into a statement about immigration by putting the Holy Family in cages.
snippet: A Methodist church in Southern California has turned a classic Christmas tradition - the Nativity scene depicting the birth of Jesus - into a statement about immigration by putting the Holy Family in cages.
lead_paragraph: CLAREMONT, Calif. — A Methodist church in Southern California has turned a classic Christmas tradition - the Nativity scene depicting the birth of Jesus - into a statement about immigration by putting the Holy Family in cages.
headline_main: Church Nativity Scene Depicts Holy Family as Caged Refugees
headline_print_headline: Church Nativity Scene Depicts Holy Family as Caged Refugees

abstract: A federal court ruled that President Trump’s proclamation of a national emergency did not justify tapping into Pentagon construction funds.
snippet: A federal court ruled that President Trump’s proclamation of a national emergency did not justify tapping into Pentagon construction funds.
lead_paragraph: A federal court in Texas issued a nationwide injunction late on Tuesday preventing the Trump administration from using $3.6 billion in military construction funds to erect a wall along the southern border, ruling that an emergency proclamation that enabled the government to access the funds was unlawful.

abstract: The legislation, responding to an investigation in The New York Times, would make tech companies more responsible for retaining data about abuse.
snippet: The legislation, responding to an investigation in The New York Times, would make tech companies more responsible for retaining data about abuse.
lead_paragraph: Legislation was introduced on Tuesday that would hold tech companies more responsible for an explosion in online child sexual abuse material and give law enforcement agencies more opportunity to gather evidence of crimes.

abstract: President Recep Tayyip Erdogan said Turkey might send troops to Libya to counter Russian-backed militia forces.
snippet: President Recep Tayyip Erdogan said Turkey might send troops to Libya to counter Russian-backed militia forces.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — The battle for control of Libya threatened to escalate further this week as Turkey said it might intervene to stop the Russian-backed forces now closing in on Tripoli, the capital.
